    <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  There is a functor 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathsf {ord} : \mathbf {Sch} \to  \mathbf {Pos} ]]></fr:tex>
  taking a scheme <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> to the poset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ord}\, X = \{x,y\in  X\mid x \le  y\}]]></fr:tex>. This functor is corepresented by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2 \cong  \operatorname {Spec} 2[x]]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2]]></fr:tex> here is the Sierpinski space.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
