              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Unlike algebraic geometry, the points of a scheme 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathsf {pt} : \mathbf {Sch} \to  \mathbf {Pos} ]]></fr:tex>
  is corepresented by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1 = \operatorname {Spec} 2]]></fr:tex>. The reason it lands in posets is only that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Sch}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Pos}]]></fr:tex>-enriched. In some sense <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2]]></fr:tex> is the unique distributive lattice which is a <html:em>field</html:em>.
</html:p>
